  "texts": [
    "This aspect remains a focus for future investigation.The resolution analysis of NaI(Tl) scintillators revealed a characteristic resolution curve that follows the 1/ N pe trend, as expected for Poisson fluctuations in N pe.",
    "Waveform simulation provided compelling confirmation of the resolution at low energies, allowing for the extension of the resolution curve to lower energy ranges.",
    "This enhancement in our ability to detect low-energy DM recoil signals is very important.The findings of this study hold significant implications for background modeling in NaI(Tl) experiments.",
    "Precise calibration and characterization of the nPR effect are essential for accurately modeling the background spectra resulting from radioactive interactions involving electrons and photons.",
    "To facilitate more detailed simulations, the integration of the nonproportional light production of NaI(Tl) into the Geant4 toolkit is under development, building on similar efforts reported previously [72,73].Furthermore, it is imperative to consider nPR calibration when interpreting signals that may come from DM interactions with electrons or photons."
  ]
